“Nice Drive” AUCTION IS LIVE FOR 24 HOURS

What an honor it was to be invited to the 2023 BMW championship. When they asked me to do a painting on site, I was of course excited. When I found out that PGA tour player, Tommy Fleetwood would be collaborating with me on this piece, I was even more stoked. 

For this painting, we utilize my splatter technique while implementing BMW’s beautiful signature colors. I don’t think Tommy would’ve ever imagined he’d be hitting paint at a canvas during a FedEx cup playoff tournament, but you could totally tell he was having a blast. 

After hacking paint at the canvas with Tommy, I was tasked to paint the BMW logo on top. Seeing as how their logo is round, it felt like the perfect fit to put the logo on a tee as if it were itself a golf ball. 

This painting will come dated, authenticated and signed by Tommy Fleetwood and myself.
All proceeds from the piece will benefit the Evans Scholars Foundation and its mission of awarding full tuition and housing college scholarships to caddies. Since 2007, the BMW Championship has contributed more than $44.5 million to fund caddie scholarships

So whether you love Tommy Fleetwood, BMW, or just my paintings in general, this piece is for you. Please bid and let’s raise money for a great cause.

Stoked on this custom commission donation for the DFW WALK To End Hydrocephalus benefiting @hydroassoc & inspired by the coolest 4 year old golfer @thedukeofclubs who was born as a micropreemie & developed Hydrocephalus because of brain bleeds he got from his prematurity. His parents were told he’d never walk or talk, but the doctors didn’t know they had a 2lb golf prodigy in the making that would overcome every obstacle to achieve his dreams. Seriously, go check out his swing the little dude is pure. His mom leads their local chapter in Dallas-Fort Worth of the Hydrocephalus Association to advocate for #HydroWarriors like Duke & fundraise to find a cure for #Hydrocephalus that will no longer involve brain surgery, which is currently the only treatment option for this condition that affects over 1 million Americans. To find out more about #hydrocephalusawareness visit the HA at the link in their bio!

I needed a win. I really did. I’ve been through a lot in this life, but I’ve never run away from the fight. This year I decided to change things up, try something new, and take a leap. Similar to when I decided to post golf trick shots for a living about 7 years ago. I didn’t know how things would pan out, but I chose happiness regardless of the consequences. Each time I have chosen happiness it has paid off. Lately I’ve been feeling a bit down and uncertain of where my life was headed. It’s a tough position to be in. Battling with what you think you should be doing vs. going out on a limb and discovering what could be. As I’ve gotten older I now know I don’t want to be the guy that’s doing just what he should. I will always challenge myself to see what else is possible. I want to look back and know I accomplished things that required more of me. I never thought I’d be a successful artist… like zero chance. Yet here we are. While I plan on maintaining this along with golf, I’m excited to see what else is possible. My finger is hammering the “fuck it” button everyday until I die. I love you all and can’t thank you enough for allowing me to continue pressing that button.
That last shot though… See you tomorrow for day 25 (which is just so fitting 🟢🔴)
MERRY CHRISTMAS!!!! Thank you all for an amazing year. See you in 2024.
